<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
A web <a title="burst" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/burst">burst</a> or rupture in web offset lithography, caused by the paper unrolling into the press's rollers at uneven speeds due to inconsistencies in a paper's thickness throughout the roll. (See <a title="Caliper" href="Caliper">Caliper</a>. See also <a title="Air Shear Burst" href="Air_Shear_Burst">Air Shear Burst</a>, <a title="Cross-Machine Tension Burst" href="Cross-Machine_Tension_Burst">Cross-Machine Tension Burst</a>, and <a title="Full Machine-Direction Burst" href="Full_Machine-Direction_Burst">Full Machine-Direction Burst</a>.) 
</p>
